title: For Sale:  Dan Wesson 4" barrel .357 Magnum (.38 Special, .38 Special +P) Range and Carry Ready with 2 Grip Sets, Speedloader
postcontent: Dan Wesson 4" .357 Magnum .38 Special .38 Special +P.  Ready for range and carry, it comes with original big (HUGE might be a better description) wood target grip, new Hogue combat monogrip, and Safariland ALS II speed loader.  Known as one of the most accurate revolvers, it was in use by an actual majority of competition sillouette shooters.  It features as fine a single action trigger as has ever come off the shelf.  One of those where it's hard to tell if you actually pressed the trigger or just thought about pressing it.  Double action trigger is pretty nice too, smooth and not too heavy.  Accuracy is also enhanced by 2 piece barrel and shroud with full top strap and full bottom strap.  A really cool and unique feature is that the barrel and shroud and changeable by end users and only needs two tools.  So it can be everything from a 2" .38 Special to an 8" .357 Magnum if you pick up the extra parts.  Finish has significant wear, although personally that doesn't bother me on mechanically strong high quality revolvers like this.  One could certainly enhance the value a lot with refinishing though since they command some very high prices when cosmetically perfect.  It's essentially an L frame S&W and will fit those holsters perfectly and many other accessories.  Works with some N frame too.  The grips change easily with a common size hex key and there are still more grips being made for it than you can shake a stick at.  These carry much better than many people imagine too.  A decent pancake holster spreads weight so well that weight really isn't a factor.  And pancakes conceal so well that with the combat grip it will pretty much disappear under just a light t-shirt for hip carry.  Anything heavier than a t-shirt and you get essentially perfect concealment while still having a ferocious and deadly accurate .357 Magnum on your hip.  All in all a very well made and very interestingly featured revolver, but I need a little room in my collection and someone else may have more use for Danny Boy.

location: Bethany / NW OKC, Oklahoma City, Oklahoma
postcontent: Ultra Rare Sino-Soviet-Albanian SKS, all Matching Numbers, Arsenal 26. This is a true first year Sino-Soviet-Albanian SKS made with all Soviet parts as indicated by the serial number, the Arsenal 26 Triangle without the Chinese writting next to it, the blade bayonet and all of the proper Russian proof marks. In addition, the rear sight also bears the Russian proof mark, the lightening cut on the bolt has the classic heavy swirl marks, indicative of a Russian bolt as opposed to the smooth surface inside the lightening cut on the Chinese bolt. The Russian-made barrel, is indicated by the extra long shoulder in front of the wrench lug where the barrel meets the receiver.  The stock with a two hole butt plate is a modification resulting from China's trade agreement with Albania in the early 70's.  Albania had specified the requirement for an extra hole in the butt plate to hold a separate oiler in addition to the cleaning kit. This is a first year Sino-Soviet SKS that was later modified by the Chinese for export to Albania. Excellent Plus Condition, probably unissued.  Has been meticulously cleaned and test fired, then re-cleaned. Also treated with Z-max Gun Metal Lubricant and Preservative.
